defaultSCRIPT Centre for IT and IP Law is an interdisciplinary research centre at the School of Law of the University of Edinburgh. Initially funded by the AHRC, it carries out research in the 
defaultintersection 
default between law, science and technology. 
defaultSince its inception
default, it organises 
default several “foresight fora” that 
defaulttry
default to anticipate emerging legal issues in the fields of internet, IP and medical law. Its current director is Prof Burkhard Schafer, who also authored this response.  
defaultIn relation to autonomous vehicles and in
defaulttelligent transport infrastructure:
default&#xa0;
default 
defaultWhat are (or were) the policy challenges presented by this technology? How have these challenges been identified?
default&#xa0;
defaultHow prepared is (or was) the Government to react to challenges presented by this techn
defaultology? How effective was this reaction?
